DECSTBM - Set Top and Bottom Margins (DEC Private)

ESC [ Pn; Pn r

    default values: see below This sequence sets the top
and bottom margins to define the scrolling region. The first parameter
is the line number of the first line in the scrolling region; the
second parameter is the line number of the bottom line in the scrolling
region. Default is the entire screen (no margins). The minimum size of
the scrolling region allowed is two lines, i.e., the top margin must be
less than the bottom margin. The cursor is placed in the home position
(see Origin Mode DECOM).

